hopobject.body: Sorry, you must have the wrong number www.everlasting-health.com.au - Consider a donor advised fund. These are charities, oftenrun by large financial companies that enable donors to lock intheir tax deductions for gifts, amass funds, and then dole themout to individual charities on their own schedule. "They aregoing gangbusters," says Palmer. Fidelity Charitable, forexample, is now the second most popular U.S. charity and raised$3.3 billion in 2012, a gain of 89 percent over the previousyear. Others are run by Charles Schwab Corp., Vanguard and T.Rowe Price Group Inc.
